Lateral region of podosoma
: Genal tooth broad, subrectangular, with dens ventrodistally, with longitudinal ridge ventrolaterally (
Figs 21E, F
). Tutorium broad, rectangular, 142–148 µm long, of which cusp 74–81 µm long, distal margin with 5–8 teeth (
Figs 21E, F
). Custodium about 58 µm long, thick along length (
Fig. 29C
). Porose area Al about 6 µm in diameter.
